{
  "name": "Reports Organization Monitor",
  "description": "Automatically monitor and organize report and summary files according to project standards",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "author": "Kiro AI Assistant",
  "when": {
    "patterns": [
      "*report*.md",
      "*summary*.md", 
      "*REPORT*.md",
      "*SUMMARY*.md",
      "*Report*.md",
      "*Summary*.md"
    ],
    "exclude_patterns": [
      "reports-summaries/**",
      ".kiro/**",
      "node_modules/**",
      "build/**",
      "gradle/**"
    ]
  },
  "then": {
    "prompt": "üîç **Report Organization Alert**\n\nA report or summary file has been detected outside the standardized `reports-summaries/` directory structure.\n\n**File detected**: {{file_path}}\n\n**Required Actions**:\n1. **Categorize**: Determine the appropriate category based on content:\n   - `architecture-design/` - Architecture and design reports\n   - `diagrams/` - Diagram-related reports  \n   - `frontend/` - Frontend development reports\n   - `infrastructure/` - Infrastructure and deployment reports\n   - `project-management/` - Project management reports\n   - `task-execution/` - Task completion reports\n   - `testing/` - Testing and QA reports\n   - `translation/` - Translation system reports\n   - `general/` - General reports\n   - `quality-ux/` - UX and quality reports\n\n2. **Move File**: Transfer to `reports-summaries/{category}/`\n3. **Update Links**: Update all references in other documents\n4. **Verify**: Ensure all links work correctly\n5. **Index**: Add to `reports-summaries/README.md` if significant\n\n**Tools Available**:\n- `scripts/organize-reports-summaries.py` - Automated organization\n- `scripts/update-report-links.py` - Link updates\n\n**Standards Reference**: `.kiro/steering/reports-organization-standards.md`\n\nPlease organize this file according to the project standards to maintain clean documentation structure."
  },
  "priority": "high",
  "tags": ["organization", "documentation", "reports", "standards"],
  "enabled": true
}